1) Git clone this repository, and 
   cd into the directory with "Dockerfile":

    git clone https://github.com/ealbin/Docker_Cassandra.git
    (data is no longer included, run/edit fetchdata.sh)

2) Install Docker:

    http://www.docker.com

3) Make a Cassandra Cluster:

    docker run --rm --name crayvault -d cassandra:latest
    (for reference: http://hub.docker.com/_/cassandra )
    
4) Build Dockerfile:
    
    docker build -t ubuntu:daq .
    
5) Boot up an instance:

    docker run --rm --name craydata --link crayvault:cassandra -it ubuntu:daq    

6) Run the test load:
    
    ipython test.py
    (in the working directory: /home/src)

7) Talk to the Cassandra container, or whatever

    docker run --it --link crayvault:cassandra --rm cassandra cqlsh cassandra
